- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also likely as the algorithm involves geometric concepts such as planar graphs. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possibility as the paper deals with graph theory and the properties of $H$-minor free graphs. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with graph theory and algorithms for solving games on graphs. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also a possibility as the paper deals with computing shortest paths in graphs with integer edge weights.
